data.title: Hidden Gem
data.text: I found this restaurant by doing a search of the area, and if I wasn't using Google Maps I would have missed it. Their staff is friendly, and the meal I had was delicious. I was very pleased I visited for lunch, and would recommend it to others.

data.title: I'm not vegan
data.text: Went here with my GF who is now vegan. Hesitant of course, I ordered the rice tacos. Not too bad, but nothing I'd get again. My GF ordered a soul food plate which was very good! The kale greens and the yams were delicious! When we return it's definitely Greens and yams for me.

data.title: Unexpected & Unassuming Hidden Gem
data.text: What a pleasant surprise! Our daughter suggested this place because of her vegan lifestyle and we agreed to go. a little our of the way and certainly not on a busy street this simple and unassuming diner will blow you away with a beautiful presentation, hot delicious food and a friendly staff.

data.title: GREAT Vegan Cuisine
data.text: We went here this weekend and got there as they opened. There were 5 of us so we decided to try as much on the menu as possible. That really paid off. There is some of the most flavorful food here. The carrot-tuna salad is amazing. So are the polenta cakes. It was all actually really good. We made the trip from San Diego. Well worth the drive!

data.title: First Vegan Meal
data.text: Flavorful, huge portion. I had been watching  this place every on yelp all the great reviews. It a small place but wow yummy meal. I think the price is worth  it. You get a ton of food! I don't know what I'd  like to try next. I called my order in, I heard it can get crowded.

data.title: Really Enjoyed This Place!
data.text: This is a  Vegan casual restaurant with no wait staff.  You order and pay at the front counter, and your food is delivered to your table.  You help yourself to water, eating utensils and napkins.  The staff taking our order was so very nice and friendly! When we questioned her on a particular item, she brought us a sample so we could try it!! We all thoroughly enjoyed our food, the servings are generous and filling. The flavors of each dish we tried were well blended and so delicious that even the meat eaters will love this place!  We were to full to try dessert, but will definitely try it on our next visit - that's right......this place is so good that we will certainly be back!!!

data.title: Fresh and tasty
data.text: I liked the feel of this restaurant as soon as I walked in.  They have an excellent menu, I had the Kilimanjaro quesadilla which was absolutely delicious.  The music added to the great atmosphere as did the art works by a local artist.

data.title: Excellent Food
data.text: The food was absolutely scrumptious while leaving a great after taste in my mouth. The staff and atmosphere were pleasantly delightful, and I look forward to visiting again the next time I'm in Inglewood.

data.title: Awesome Vegan
data.text: I am always thrilled to find a new vegan restaurant. The owner Babette is there greeting people and is hands on. She is fantastic. The food is made with love and how fun to get comfort food that is cruelty free! I had the soul food platter and I could not resist a slice of sweet potato pie.

data.title: Great food and I'm not Vegan!!!!
data.text:
While visiting the Los Angeles area we decided to find a Vegan restaurant due to a family member fasting. We found this restaurant on our search and decided to give it a try. Not sure what it's like on a busy day and what time that would be but we stopped by on a Tuesday around 1pm and there were a few patrons inside. Good for us because we had time to decided what we wanted from the menu and spent very little time standing in line to place our order. By the way, the food concept is Southern Food Vegan style. After finding something that sounded like a good o' home cooked meal and finding something my wife and kid would like we were ready to order. We ended up ordering the Organic Soul Food Platter for my wife and the Lunch Burrito for me. 

I haven't been a fan of Tofu but the bbq tofu on the Organic Soul Food Platter made me think that maybe I can go Vegan. I wasn't a big fan of the mac and cheese and the cornbread reminded me almost of a whole grain or bran muffin which was pretty good. I had the lunch burrito which I just couldn't put down. That was one of the best burritos I've ever had. The burrito came with chips which my 3 year old devoured. For drinks we had the Beet Lemonade and water. That was one of the best servings of beets I've ever had. My wife and I honestly weren't sure at first but was itching to order a second drink.

All-in-all the food was great, and the service was excellent. By the way, the food was so good my wife and I didn't even realize we ate each others orders. We'll have to make a stop when we're back in town and try out more of the menu.

data.title: A Gem For Vegans, Vegetarians, & People Who Love FOOD
data.text: I was relatively new to the vegan lifestyle and this restaurant helped me stay committed and changed what I believed what it meant to be vegan.  The Enchilada Pie is sooooo awesome. All of the deserts are great! The food is so great, it's hard to believe this is a Vegan restaurant.  If you love to eat and if you just love food, this is the place for you.  After leaving Los Angeles, I was so disappointed because I couldn't find a Vegan restaurant that came anywhere close to being this great.

data.title: Best steamed greens I've ever had!
data.text: The menu is full of great tasting, plant based options. The pictures don't do it justice. The staff was very helpful and patient while we tried to decide what to have. In the end, everything we tried was great. Given the chance, I'd go back in a heartbeat.

data.title: So good
data.text:
A friend posted a video about this place on fb last week and it looked good so we decided to try it out today. I like to try new things and to support small businesses. Neither of us is vegan or even vegetarian. We shared the carrot croquettes and the soul food platter, with a piece of carrot cake for dessert. The carrot croquettes were really good, and they came with two polenta cakes with gravy. I have no idea what that gravy was made from but it was delicious. That might have been my favorite part of the meal. The soul food platter comes with a nice variety of stuff, including some mac & cheese. I have eaten vegan "cheese" before and it's gross, so this mac & cheese was quite a surprise. It was almost magical, because there was none of that weird vegan cheese taste to it. If you like kale, the greens were good. I'm just not a fan of kale or greens in general. The black eyed peas were delicious. The cole slaw and potato salad would have been great if not for the bell peppers. Carrot cake normally comes with a cream cheese frosting, but this was different. I don't know what was on there but it was good. There was pineapple involved. It wasn't too sweet, which made it even better. 

The service was very friendly and good. You order at a counter and they bring the food to you. The lady who took our order and the man who brought the food to the table were both super nice. When I mentioned to the waiter that the gravy was so delicious, he suggested I return for the biscuits and gravy. 

It's on a block that seems to be going through a revitalization. The surrounding neighborhood is really nice. Across the street is a boarded up old theater; I hope someone renovates it and brings it back to its glory. Inside the restaurant, it's kind of Spartan but not in a bad way. There is a little living room sort of area at the front where you can hang out with your friends and talk, apart from the tables. The art on the walls is nice, and the music is good. Even the bathroom was nice.

If you find yourself in Inglewood or you need to go to LAX, I would highly recommend a meal here. Even a meat eater like me can enjoy it. I'm looking forward to going back.

The owner of the place said in the video I saw that she is 64. I found that hard to believe. Seeing her in person makes it even harder to believe. I would guess she's in her early 40s. Maybe all that vegan eating is doing it.

data.title: Great Find Near LAX
data.text:
Came here before an LAX flight and I'm so happy I did. It's a 100% vegan restaurant. The vegan soul food platter was delicious. The best parts to me were the cold portions, a slaw and a potato salad, but I enjoyed all of it. It was enough to take home leftovers.  

The meal was balanced with both an assortment of veggies, tofu, beans, and yummy starches.

The ambiance is hip and relaxed. I took a good long meal there by myself, enjoying the artwork on the walls and relaxing with my book as I ate. 

The restaurant is also very easily accessible by several local buses, which was handy coming from an airport hotel.

data.title: No frills, but really good food.
data.text:
Stopped here after arriving at LAX near dinner time and didn't want to hop on the freeway.  I am not a vegan, just an omnivore.  The neighborhood is not fancy, but parking was right on the street at the front door.  There were a couple other diners in the place when we (3) arrived.  I didn't know what to expect.  The interior is kind of stark, and you walk up to the counter at the back, look at the menu and order the food.  I never knew that there could be a vegan soul food cuisine.  The food here was delicious.  Each of us ordered something different and each of us was well pleased with the quality and quantity of the serving.  I would go out of my way to dine here in the future.

The place was clean, service was cordial.  I would say that service was slow, except that since each plate is prepared from scratch, the delay was about right, and the food was well worth waiting for.  The prices were low, so the combination of low price with high quality means that the value is way up there.

data.title: Nice vegan soul by LAX
data.text: Had a great vegan soul food meal after landing at LAX and was starving. Love their take on Mac and no cheese and the greens are awesome!

data.title: Extremely unprofessional behavior
data.text: Unfortunately I'll review their behavior over their food, which is good if a bit overpriced.  For several years they've let us advertise our events and we've had them cater our events (I book programming for the Inglewood Public Library two blocks away.)  Today the owner refused to accept some of our flyers, gave no logical reason except he "didn't know about it", and closed the door on me not once, but twice.  I've been a public librarian for 25 years and dealt with everyone from the homeless to our Congresswoman, and no one has been so inexplicably and unprofessionally rude.  I've removed them from our recommendations online, removed them from our catering list, and I won't ever eat there again myself.

data.title: Dead on for vegan soul food
data.text:
Great food.  Nice peaceful atmosphere.  I am a little bummed because I couldn't taste the food fully (I came down with a respiratory infection so my taste buds were all out of whack).

I can say that my husband loved his enchilladas.  I ordered the soul food plate.  My sweet receptors seemed to working just fine because the BBQ tofu, mac and cheese, and sweet potatoes were all scrumptious.  The rest was good, too, but I didn't enjoy them half as much as the sweet potatoes and mac and cheese.  Those were divine.

data.title: Sooo good!
data.text: Found it on holy cow. Had a hard time finding it...drove by 3 times but once there had gorgeous lunch!!

data.title: I am in love...
data.text:
This place is AMAZING. I recommend going with a big appetite--the portions are huge, usually enough for 2 people! Everything I have tried has been delicious. You can tell the food is made with love and pride. I make sure to stop here every time I fly out of LAX to fill up with scrumptious and healthy vegan foods pre-flights. I love how every dish is filled with many flavors and wholesome ingredients. There are so many amazing options, it is always hard to choose. I can't wait to go back! 

There's not much to comment on in terms of service--dude at the counter seems nice enough, servers don't do much but deliver your food but seem pleasant. I don't have anything bad to say about the service, but it doesn't stand out either. They get the job done, the thing to look forward to is the spectacular food.
